quran[11]{c,v,t,f}:
  96,16,"by the lying forelock steeped in sin.{1}",footnotes:1:[The forelock here implies the person with the forelock.]
  96,17,"So let him summon his helpmates;{1}",footnotes:1:[As we have explained in the Introduction]
  96,18,"We too shall summon the guards of Hell.{1}",footnotes:1:[According to the explanation given by Qatadah]
  99,7,"So, whoever does an atom's weight of good shall see it;"
  99,8,"and whoever does an atom's weight of evil shall see it.{1}",footnotes:1:[A simple and straightforward meaning of this statement]
  100,4,"and blaze a trail of dust,"
  100,5,"and penetrate deep into a host."
  100,6,"Verily man is most ungrateful to his Lord;{1}",footnotes:1:[This is for which an oath has been sworn by the horses]
  101,1,"The Calamity!{1}",footnotes:1:[Qariah literally means the striking one. Qar is to strike one thing upon another so severely as to produce a noise. In view of this literal meaning]
  101,2,"What is the Calamity?"
  101,3,"And what do you know what the Calamity is?"
